 For the Middelburgers who have registered and who are ready to vote, here is what you need to know.
The IEC has ensured that voting is as easy as possible for you, with plenty of voting stations all around Middelburg. The list of voting stations are as follows: Ward 10:
Eastdene Community Hall, 92 Verdoorn Street, Eastdene.
The Christian Bible Church, Rondebosch. Ward 11:
Faith Revival Miracle Centre, Hope City. Ward 12:
Corpus Christi Church, 23 Kransberg Street, Aerorand. Ward 13:
Laerskool CR Swart, 30A Suid Street, CBD.
Bezuidenhout Hall, Lilian Ngoyi Street, CBD.
Middelburg Primary School, John Magagula Street, CBD. Ward 14:
Middelburg Provincial Hospital (A tent will be erected as a voting station), Clubville.
NG Kerk, cnr of Cowen Ntuli- and Gustav Preller Street, Clubville. Ward 15:
Hoërskool and Laerskool Kanonkop.
Middelburg Correctional Centre, cnr of Hoop- and Coetzee Street. Ward 16:
Dennesig Park, next to Church of Today.
Laerskool Dennesig. • There will also be multiple voting stations in the surrounding areas of Middelburg, including Nasaret, Hlalamnandi, Extention 24, Mhluzi and Doornkop. Keep an eye out for our #IMadeMyMark election supplement full of fantastic election content in this week’s Middelburg Observer.
